    "created_at": "2015-12-17T08:37:44Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-12-17T08:37:44Z",
    "body": "I think we should only add new APIs when:\n1. a job can not be done with existing APIs, like `Menu.sendActionToFirstResponder`,\n2. there is a common pattern for certain jobs, like `Menu.buildFromTemplate`.\n\nHiding an app doesn't belong to either condition, it can be done with existing APIs, and on Windows and Linux it is a rather rare task.\n\nThe only reason I think we can add `app.show/hide` APIs on OS X is, hiding/showing an app is kind of common task on this platform.\n"
  },
